The electric field part of an electromagnetic wave in a medium is represented by E<sub>x</sub> = 0;
<br><br>$${E_y} = 2.5{N \over C}\cos \left[ {\left( {2\pi  \times {{10}^6}{{rad} \over m}} \right)t - \left( {\pi  \times {{10}^{ - 2}}{{rad} \over s}} \right)x} \right];$$
<br><br>E<sub>z</sub> = 0.
